WEBVTT

00:00.098 --> 00:02.222
Today, we're gonna be in Joshua chapter six.

00:02.242 --> 00:03.824
We're gonna talk about Jericho.

00:03.905 --> 00:14.543
Most of you, probably, if you've been going to church for any length of time, especially if you grew up in church, are almost certainly gonna be familiar with the story of the fall of Jericho.

00:15.485 --> 00:19.492
Have you ever been in a place where you felt like you were out of resources?

00:20.453 --> 00:25.362
You know, when you have pushed everything that you have to the very edge

00:25.602 --> 00:31.388
And the problem is still not solved, and you're kind of like, oh my gosh, I don't know what I'm gonna do now.

00:32.349 --> 00:37.194
And in a spiritual sense, that's right where God wants us, right?

00:37.675 --> 00:43.741
We're gonna talk about a different way to handle those kinds of seemingly insurmountable objects and odds today.

00:44.382 --> 00:45.383
But we've all been there.

00:45.403 --> 00:52.530
I heard about this young man that he had worked on the railroad for years, and he said he wanted a job as a signalman.

00:52.866 --> 00:57.451
And so for his interview, he was told to meet the inspector at the signal box.

00:58.092 --> 01:04.840
The inspector asked him, he said, what would you do if you realized the two trains were heading toward each other on the same track?

01:05.761 --> 01:07.443
The young man said, well, that's easy.

01:07.523 --> 01:10.346
I would switch the points for one of the trains.

01:11.387 --> 01:13.810
The inspector said, well, what if that lever was broken?

01:15.071 --> 01:20.818
He said, the young man said, then I jumped down out of the signal box and I'd use the manual lever over there.

01:21.570 --> 01:26.016
Then the inspector said, what if that lever had been struck by lightning?

01:27.058 --> 01:33.647
The young man said, well, then I would run to the signal box and phone the next signal box to let him know what was happening.

01:34.629 --> 01:37.813
Inspector continued and he said, well, what if that phone was busy?

01:39.015 --> 01:46.446
The young man said, well, in that case I get down out of the signal box and use the public emergency phone at the crossing up there.

01:47.788 --> 01:49.330
Then the inspector said, well,

01:49.954 --> 01:54.643
What would you do if the public emergency phone had been vandalized?"

01:54.663 --> 01:59.412
The young man said, well, he said, I guess I'd run to town and get my dad.

01:59.452 --> 02:03.180
And the inspector was a little confused.

02:03.200 --> 02:05.063
And he said, well, why would you go get your dad?

02:05.083 --> 02:10.674
And he said, well, he ain't never seen two trains crash before.

02:14.754 --> 02:23.463
You know, all of us, right, when we come to the end of our resources and we don't know what the next step is, you know, we rely on God, we depend on God.

02:23.883 --> 02:34.994
Sometimes when we come to the end of our own resources, we just get angry because we have done everything that we have, we can do or know to do and the situation is not a lot better.

02:35.014 --> 02:42.482
I mean, one, you know, one time Becky almost got divorced just saying the blinds in our house and

02:42.818 --> 02:49.107
I mean, I'd come to the end of my rope on hanging those blinds and trying to get them, you know, straight and all that kind of thing.

02:49.548 --> 03:00.625
And when I'd come to the end of all of my resources, I was just ticked off, you know, and I think she was ticked off probably more so at me than the situation, but I was ticked off.

03:00.965 --> 03:07.976
Some people will just sit back like this operator and say, well, a crash is going to happen for sure because I wasn't able to stop it.

03:08.016 --> 03:09.618
I wasn't able to prevent it.

03:10.594 --> 03:14.961
And this, you know, all of us need to think to ourselves, is there a better way to do that?

03:14.981 --> 03:27.261
Is there a better way to handle the crisis in our life or the obstacles in our lives, the Jericho's in our lives apart from using only our own resources?

03:28.242 --> 03:30.366
That's a question that all of us need to ask.

03:30.886 --> 03:35.634
It's also a question that any individual or every church needs to ask.

03:36.098 --> 03:41.206
which is one of the questions is, are we content to remain the same way that we are?

03:42.167 --> 03:46.514
You know, spiritually am I content to remain the same way that I am?

03:46.574 --> 03:49.779
Now I know that I have not arrived, right?

03:49.839 --> 03:52.683
Nobody arrives until they get to heaven.

03:53.324 --> 03:57.931
And then the sanctification of God making me more like Jesus is finished.

03:58.432 --> 03:59.954
But up until that time,

04:00.162 --> 04:03.045
in my content to stay the same way that I am now.

04:03.145 --> 04:07.550
And the answer for all of us in this room ought to be a resounding no.

04:07.570 --> 04:09.412
I want to keep growing.

04:09.452 --> 04:10.574
I want to keep learning.

04:10.634 --> 04:11.755
I want to keep singing.

04:12.175 --> 04:13.617
I want to keep praising the Lord.

04:13.677 --> 04:15.099
I want to keep being thankful.

04:15.439 --> 04:16.981
I want to learn to be more humble.

04:17.021 --> 04:19.103
It should be all of those things.

04:20.124 --> 04:22.867
And a church has to answer the same question.

04:23.668 --> 04:28.754
Churches face obstacles just like individual people face obstacles.

04:29.026 --> 04:33.773
If your church is against an obstacle, are we willing to stay the same way we have been?

04:33.833 --> 04:36.176
Or do we want to continue to grow?

04:36.276 --> 04:46.430
Because listen friends, one thing that we're gonna learn about this story in Jericho is that God does not ask you to do anything very often that's super easy, right?

04:47.231 --> 04:49.674
A lot of the things he asks you to do are hard.

04:50.576 --> 04:53.480
And you don't know how you can accomplish them in your own will.

04:53.520 --> 04:56.584
You don't know how you can accomplish them in your own strength.

04:56.624 --> 04:58.226
And the reason is you can't.

04:58.594 --> 05:03.822
And we're gonna see that two different times, maybe three different times here in this story.

05:04.864 --> 05:10.813
What we are gonna see is that neither Joshua nor the children of Israel fought the battle, right?

05:10.873 --> 05:21.509
The battle had already been, the battle, the outcome was not in question by the time Joshua and the Israelite army arrived at Jericho.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.312
God already had a plan.

05:23.372 --> 05:24.734
He already had a purpose.

05:25.114 --> 05:27.538
He already knew what it was that he was gonna do.

05:27.970 --> 05:31.174
He knew that the battle was the lords.

05:31.194 --> 05:37.382
And so in chapter six, we see that the time has come from the people of Israel to leave the desert.

05:38.203 --> 05:45.873
And it almost seems like God is taking him right back where they were at the time of the rebellion as he leads them through the Jordan River.

05:45.893 --> 05:50.459
And they're in the same spot as the previous generation, right?

05:50.479 --> 05:53.904
They're at the water's edge and they have to, they have to make a decision.

05:53.984 --> 05:55.826
And the decision is, what are we going to do?

05:56.738 --> 06:00.262
Are we going to follow God who has led us up to this point?

06:00.282 --> 06:06.830
Or are we going to go our own way and do our own thing and see what happens?

06:06.850 --> 06:10.855
And so the question we ask ourselves is how am I doing spiritually?

06:10.895 --> 06:14.479
Am I moving ahead or am I falling behind?

06:14.599 --> 06:18.724
And the thing that we need to ask ourselves as a church, how are we doing spiritually?

06:19.305 --> 06:23.730
Are we going ahead or are we falling behind?

06:26.402 --> 06:34.510
I've heard it said that most people would rather stay in the certainty of misery than move to the misery of uncertainty.

06:35.991 --> 06:36.872
And that's true.

06:38.253 --> 06:46.621
A lot of people spend their whole lives staying in the misery of certainty because then at least then they know what to expect.

06:48.022 --> 06:56.370
But they're petrified to take the next step of obedience because they're afraid they may experience the misery of uncertainty.

06:57.154 --> 07:09.169
I've seen people live through terribly devastating things in their lives because they couldn't move forward, because they couldn't get out of the box that they had put themselves in.

07:09.229 --> 07:10.851
And they knew what God wanted them to do.

07:10.871 --> 07:23.346
And they knew what God wanted was the next step, but they were just terrified to take that step because they couldn't see how in my strength, how am I as a human going to be able to do that?

07:23.522 --> 07:26.346
without understanding that you don't have to do it at all.

07:26.426 --> 07:28.268
It's just, it's God who's going to do it.

07:28.608 --> 07:30.691
You just have to take a step.

07:32.013 --> 07:39.702
And so when we look at this and we talk about the fall of Jericho, you know, I want you to ask yourself, what is my personal Jericho?

07:40.944 --> 07:49.074
You know, what is it in my life that stands as an obstacle to keeping me from entering into all that God has promised to me?

07:49.826 --> 07:56.699
I mean, God has promised great and amazing and beautiful things and He wants us to be able to access those promises.

07:57.280 --> 08:00.546
He wants us to be able to live an abundant life right now.

08:01.007 --> 08:01.908
How do you do that?

08:02.790 --> 08:04.694
I mean, it could be an inner Jericho.

08:05.215 --> 08:06.597
It may be a thought pattern.

08:06.637 --> 08:07.819
It may be a temperament.

08:07.840 --> 08:13.490
It may be a personality characteristic that you want to change that's keeping you from moving on.

08:14.530 --> 08:22.418
We need to find out how the walls of that Jericho and your heart and in my heart and in this church or anywhere else we find them can fall down.

08:23.599 --> 08:25.281
It might be an outer Jericho.

08:25.501 --> 08:30.266
It may be something in front of you that somebody else has caused and you're the victim of that.

08:31.667 --> 08:33.749
And God wants you to forgive them.

08:34.130 --> 08:38.214
