That's the key.

43:26.855 --> 43:29.258
And that the power of the enemy is too great for you.

43:29.298 --> 43:33.904
If you're Jericho is to fall, then somehow God must bring it about.

43:35.086 --> 43:51.346
He said, I believe that before God entrusts any of his people with a real measure of spiritual power, victory and blessing, he brings them to a place where they have surveyed Jericho for so long that they have come to see that its conquest is absolutely hopeless.

43:51.906 --> 43:53.989
Are you in that place today?

43:55.372 --> 44:03.666
God expects nothing more from us than failure, yet we spend years trying to make ourselves something other than a failure.

44:04.547 --> 44:12.420
So as long as we think we can do it on our own strength alone, the miraculous resources of God cannot help us.

44:13.522 --> 44:18.450
When you get to the end of your rope, my friends, you're right where God wants you to be.

44:19.298 --> 44:26.728
Listen, if you have a personal Jericho that you want to pray about, grab somebody in your pews to pray with somebody next to them.

44:26.789 --> 44:28.631
You can come down to the altar and pray.

44:29.052 --> 44:31.255
Pastor Tim and I'll be back there to pray.

44:31.315 --> 44:33.037
You can grab Josh to pray.

44:33.097 --> 44:34.560
Grab one of the elders to pray.

44:35.120 --> 44:40.167
But if this message hits a home where you say, man, I've got a personal Jericho, I need to deal with.

44:40.768 --> 44:43.212
Today's the day to deal with it.

44:43.232 --> 44:47.698
As our band comes up to play our closing song, I would close this in prayer.

44:48.770 --> 44:52.756
Father God, we thank you, Lord, that you don't leave us outside the walls of Jericho.

44:54.458 --> 44:57.643
Oftentimes, God, you'll let us get to the end of our own resources.

44:57.723 --> 45:11.362
We'll get to the end of all we think we know and all that we think we can do, God, and we find you sitting there waiting for us to trust you, waiting for us to give it all into your power, your strength, your mercy, and your might.

45:11.402 --> 45:13.084
God, we trust you completely.

45:13.745 --> 45:17.010
Let us lean on you, God, in your own personal Jericho's.

45:17.186 --> 45:29.722
And Lord, as we face Jericho's in this church, let us band together in unity and cooperation to do what it is that you have called us to do, even if it may seem impossible in our own resources.

45:30.743 --> 45:31.444
We believe you.

45:31.484 --> 45:33.407
You're the God of miracles.

45:34.288 --> 45:35.810
We thank you for the scarlet thread.

45:36.691 --> 45:38.513
We pray these things in Jesus name.

45:38.873 --> 45:39.314
Amen.

